7. Charles Goodyear invented vulcanized rubber (the durable rubber we use for tires). He was trying for years to create weather-proof rubber for housing, when he accidentally dropped regular rubber mixed with sulfur onto a hot stove. This created the strong rubber we know today.

6. John Hopps invented the pacemaker by accident, when trying to artificially raise body temperatures to treat hypothermia.

During his experiment, he realized if a heart stopped beating due to cooling, it could be started again by artificial stimulation.

5. Ichiro Endo accidentally left a hot iron on his ink pen.

Due to the heat pressure, the ink pen started dropping ink from its point, dropping all over his desk. This incident gave him the initial idea to create inkjet printers.

4. Edward Benedictus accidentally knocked over a glass flask, but he noticed it retained its shape instead of shattering.

He learned there was a cellulose nitrate coating inside the glass. He went on to experiment further with this and invented bullet-proof glass.
3. Matti Makkonen was hired by Nokia to create an easier way for deaf people to communicate. He invented SMS text messaging.
2. Vint Cerf was hard of hearing and wanted a way to share information and documents with colleagues instead of phone calls. He co-created the internet.

Here's a thread of setbacks that changed the world, because I find this stuff cool:
